               <head>Letters of Surup Ram</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Riyāz̤ al-inbisāṭ by Surūp Rām ibn Mūhan Rām</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100074 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85104368 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85129379" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_465-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7623">Surūp Rām ibn Mūhan Rām</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f7623">سروپ رام</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21759">Riyāz̤ al-inbisāṭ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21759">ریاض الانبساط</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Varied work in refined prose or inshāʾ, firstly, eulogising the town of <placeName>Nuzhatnagar</placeName>
                           <placeName>Narnaul</placeName> (<placeName>Haryana State</placeName>), secondly, a collection of brief correspondence and poems and, thirdly, an essay on the blessings of good counsel. The khātimah discusses, along with other writers, the works of <persName key="viaf_5150639" role="ant">Abū al-Faz̤l</persName>, <persName key="viaf_30145911203827062840" role="ant">Ẓuhūrī</persName>, and <persName key="viaf_78539695" role="ant">Ṭughrā</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The author Sarup or <persName key="person_f7623" role="aut">Surup Ram ibn Mohan Ram</persName> completed the work in 1165/1741, reaffirmed in the chronogrammatic title 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work is divided into four faṣl, each subdivided into two sections </p>
                        <p>Dated: Ṣafar 1174/1760 </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
